person who really inspired

00:20:05.060 --> 00:20:06.800
me to actually pick up
my camera and actually

00:20:06.800 --> 00:20:09.370
be creative with it, rather than
just take happy snaps with it.

00:20:09.370 --> 00:20:10.760
Photography has changed
my life, I'm now

00:20:10.760 --> 00:20:12.100
in the process of
building a full-on photo

00:20:12.100 --> 00:20:14.160
studio at my dad's
video production studio,

00:20:14.160 --> 00:20:15.910
and I'm actually becoming a
known photographer around town.

00:20:15.910 --> 00:20:17.685
That is all thanks
to you inspiring me

00:20:17.685 --> 00:20:19.310
with your creativity
and awesome skill.

00:20:19.310 --> 00:20:21.300
Even on the days when
I can't get out of bed

00:20:21.300 --> 00:20:23.540
or I'm stuck at the hospital
or doctor's appointment,

00:20:23.540 --> 00:20:24.730
I'm planning out my next shoot.

00:20:24.730 --> 00:20:26.235
And this again is
all thanks to you.

00:20:26.235 --> 00:20:28.318
You inspire me to keep
fighting and keep shooting.

00:20:28.318 --> 00:20:29.344
Thank you so much.

00:20:29.344 --> 00:20:31.010
And I think that was
like the first time

00:20:31.010 --> 00:20:34.150
that someone had actually
said "you've changed my life"

00:20:34.150 --> 00:20:34.650
like that.

00:20:34.650 --> 00:20:36.720
What you're doing--
even if it had nothing

00:20:36.720 --> 00:20:39.174
to do with what he was doing--
really made the difference.

00:20:39.174 --> 00:20:41.090
And then suddenly that
sense of responsibility

00:20:41.090 --> 00:20:44.592
of knowing that people
are looking up to me

00:20:44.592 --> 00:20:47.690
and really paying attention
to what I was doing

00:20:47.690 --> 00:20:49.160
