00:22:52.990 --> 00:22:56.862
And he's got fibromyalgia,
super sick, bedridden guy.

00:22:56.862 --> 00:22:58.320
And I didn't know
this at the time,

00:22:58.320 --> 00:22:59.986
but he's probably one
of my hugest fans.

00:22:59.986 --> 00:23:02.202
He's read like every single
one of my Facebook posts,

00:23:02.202 --> 00:23:03.160
blog posts, everything.

00:23:03.160 --> 00:23:04.535
He knew everything
about my life.

00:23:04.535 --> 00:23:06.460
It was crazy.

00:23:06.460 --> 00:23:08.617
And instead of just
showing up at his place,

00:23:08.617 --> 00:23:10.575
I decided to just drag
him out on an adventure.

00:23:10.575 --> 00:23:12.239
So we did a photo
shoot with him.

00:23:12.239 --> 00:23:13.780
I took pictures of
him and his sister

00:23:13.780 --> 00:23:16.142
like dragging him
through the mud.

00:23:16.142 --> 00:23:18.350
He's from Australia, he's
never seen a wild kangaroo.

00:23:18.350 --> 00:23:19.596
So we saw a wild kangaroo.

00:23:19.596 --> 00:23:20.720
He'd never been to a rodeo.

00:23:20.720 --> 00:23:21.295
We brought him to a rodeo.

00:23:21.295 --> 00:23:23.253
He'd never been on a
canoes since he was seven.

00:23:23.253 --> 00:23:24.360
And he wouldn't do that.

00:23:24.360 --> 00:23:26.610
I put together a photo shoot
so that he could actually

00:23:26.610 --> 00:23:28.270
attend it and see
what that was like.

00:23:28.270 --> 00:23:31.280
So it was exactly what
I normally did, and I

00:23:31.280 --> 00:23:33.110
did the behind the
scenes and everything,

00:23:33.110 --> 00:23:35.900
but this time around, it
actually really, really made

00:23:35.900 --> 00:23:37.589
an impact on this
one individual.

00:23:37.589 --> 00:23:39.380
And I thought that was
a fascinating story.

00:23:39.380 --> 00:23:43.091
So it's been a very,
very fun process,

00:23:43.091 --> 00:23:44.590
this whole evolution
of photography.

00:23:44.590 --> 00:23:46.548
So what I'm trying to
say at the end of the day

00:23:46.548 --> 00:23:49.890
is that photography is not
just clicking the button.

00:23:49.890 --> 00:23:52.820
For me, it's not about framing
a shot and clicking it.

00:23:52.820 --> 00:23:54.700
That process just
happens to be incidental,

00:23:54.700 --> 00:23:57.380
because it is the
vehicle for which I

00:23:57.380 --> 00:23:59.222
can do all the things
that I love to do.

00:23:59.222 --> 00:24:00.930
And I think that's
the same for everybody

00:24:00.930 --> 00:24:01.846
who picks up a camera.

00:24:01.846 --> 00:24:04.735
They don't pick it up because
they want to press that button.

00:24:04.735 --> 00:24:07.110
They pick it up because they
want to showcase an emotion.

00:24:07.110 --> 00:24:08.818
They want to transport
people to a place.

00:24:08.818 --> 00:24:11.560
They want to capture beauty
in some way, shape, or form.

00:24:11.560 --> 00:24:14.524
They want to show something
that doesn't exist.

00:24:14.524 --> 00:24:15.940
They want to create
something new.

00:24:15.940 --> 00:24:18.022
So photography has reasons.

00:24:18.022 --> 00:24:19.730
There's a reason why
you love photography

00:24:19.730 --> 00:24:21.146
and why it's special
to you, and I

00:24:21.146 --> 00:24:22.860
think it's always
important to remember

00:24:22.860 --> 00:24:25.940
what those reasons are.

00:24:25.940 --> 00:24:26.440
Questions?

