00:24:44.530 --> 00:24:47.960
What was it inside of you
that made that happen?

00:24:47.960 --> 00:24:50.570
BEN VON WONG: I got bored
of engineering, and I quit.

00:24:50.570 --> 00:24:54.100
And then incidentally, I became
a photographer by default,

00:24:54.100 --> 00:24:56.310
because that was the
only thing I was doing.

00:24:56.310 --> 00:24:58.475
It wasn't really planned.

00:24:58.475 --> 00:24:59.600
I got bored of engineering.

00:24:59.600 --> 00:25:01.433
But I actually go over
that in the next part

00:25:01.433 --> 00:25:03.790
where I can talk
about the timeline.

00:25:03.790 --> 00:25:05.628
Cool?

00:25:05.628 --> 00:25:07.860
So I'll move forward.

00:25:07.860 --> 00:25:12.260
So I have this quote
from Ernest Hemingway,

00:25:12.260 --> 00:25:14.740
and it says, "It is good to
have an end to journey towards,

00:25:14.740 --> 00:25:16.930
but it is the journey
that matters in the end."

00:25:16.930 --> 00:25:19.480
and I think that just a
really important quote,

00:25:19.480 --> 00:25:21.480
because at the end of the
day, I think something

00:25:21.480 --> 00:25:25.392
that I realized along the way is
that you spend a lot more time

00:25:25.392 --> 00:25:26.850
trying to get to
somewhere than you

00:25:26.850 --> 00:25:28.770
do when actually
spending time there.

00:25:28.770 --> 00:25:32.630
And it's kind of funny, because
you set these really lofty

00:25:32.630 --> 00:25:35.244
goals, and then
suddenly you reach them.

00:25:35.244 --> 00:25:36.910
And then you need to
set something else,

00:25:36.910 --> 00:25:38.120
because there's nothing
else to do about it,

00:25:38.120 --> 00:25:39.170
because you've
already achieved it.

00:25:39.170 --> 00:25:40.620
And it gets really boring.

00:25:40.620 --> 00:25:42.286
And if anything--
in my case, I've

00:25:42.286 --> 00:25:44.160
found it disappointing
once I've achieved it,

00:25:44.160 --> 00:25:45.035
because I'm like that's it?

00:25:45.035 --> 00:25:47.659
I've gotten there already, then
just try to keep aiming higher.

00:25:47.659 --> 00:25:49.730
So I think it's always
really important

00:25:49.730 --> 00:25:52.460
to realize what you've
achieved up to now,

00:25:52.460 --> 00:25:54.040
where it's brought
you, and it just

00:25:54.040 --> 00:25:55.998
makes life a lot more
interesting along the way

00:25:55.998 --> 00:25:58.540
if you can just
reach these points.

